Recent bombings in India, including the tragic attack in Jaipur, have left at least 80 dead and 200 wounded.
The bombings, attributed to foreign-based Islamic militant groups, targeted crowded markets and temples.
International condemnation poured in, with the US, UK, and France expressing solidarity with India.
The attacks aim to sow sectarian discord and disrupt peace efforts.
The historic city of Jaipur, a major tourist destination, now mourns the loss of innocent lives.
Authorities are on high alert, urging calm and unity in the face of terrorism.
